{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee83a8fb-27fd-459d-98c4-eb1e633850d0","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is an executable. The flow is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nThis launches the test project as an app (via the testing platform), and the hot reload extension watches for file changes, re-running affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` does **not** enable hot reload — it runs tests in a one-shot batch mode without the file-watching loop that hot reload requires.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b875714f-0399-438b-86a7-eecd6480c7eb","outputTokens":136},"id":"08f4b41a-8d95-4b40-b1ba-30bbd6a2daae","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:21:06.540Z","parentId":"ae9f7f40-4682-4995-9cfc-f167d27d86a1"}
